Hourly Wage Rate Categorized

Hourly Wage Rate Categorized: 

Drag and drop Employee Count in column Shelves and category department name company name in row shelves.

Drag Company Name in Filters and right click on Company Name and Select edit filters. go to Top and select By field  by top 10 Category then click OK



Drag Calculated Field Department Name Categorized in Filters. right click and edit filters and checked True then Click OK.




Drag hourly wages in Label and in Color


Drag Hourly Wage  in Marks (Label T)  



Created calculated field (Hourly Wage Rate):

Syntax If ([Hourly Wage])>40 THEN 'TopPay' ELSEIF

([Hourly Wage]) < 30 THEN 'AvgPay'

ELSE 'Regular'

END


Calculated department name Department Categorize.

Syntax

IF

(

 CONTAINS ([Department Name], 'Accounting') OR

 CONTAINS ([Department Name],'Administration') OR

 CONTAINS ([Department Name],'Marketing') OR

 CONTAINS ([Department Name],'Operations') OR

 CONTAINS ([Department Name],'Production') OR

 CONTAINS ([Department Name],'Purchasing')

)

THEN 'True'

ELSE 'False'

END
